comments.body:
@vitalybuka @fmayer Could you please review this fix for #178576?

The issue is that stack safety analysis marks allocas as "safe" even when their address escapes to a callee. This causes ASan to skip instrumenting the alloca (no shadow memory init), but the callee's accesses are still instrumented, leading to shadow memory checks on uninitialized memory and potential false positives.

The fix adds a check to ensure the alloca's address doesn't escape (`Calls.empty()`) before marking it as safe.
